OKLAHOMA CITY — The NBA season has been suspended indefinitely after a Utah Jazz player, whom the Deseret News has confirmed through league sources is center Rudy Gobert, tested positive Wednesday for COVID-19.
“The NBA announced that a player on the Utah Jazz has preliminarily tested positive for COVID-19,” the league said in an announcement.
“A preliminary positive result came back right before tip-off of the Utah Jazz-Oklahoma City game.
Utah Jazz G-League team had game canceled tonight against Phoenix Suns G-League team in Arizona.
“The preliminary positive result came back just before tip-off of the Utah Jazz-Oklahoma City game, and we have been in touch since that time.